00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:23,000
 They're taking notice?

726
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:28,000
 Because that's what was happening, according to the goodness of God, in the people of Israel's life, according to Nehemiah.

727
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,000
 Maybe it's dancing. Someone said that.

728
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:36,000
 David was so thrilled the ark had come back to Israel that he danced with all his might before the Lord.

729
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:39,000
 I have never danced with all my might.

730
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:43,000
 That would be a sight to behold, and one which you will not.

731
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:46,000
 And yet, we should do it!

732
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:53,000
 Like, we should be willing to undignify ourselves in the spirit of rejoicing at God and who he is.

733
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:55,000
 He's so good, we should.

734
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:59,000
 Laughter. Like, it's one of the best witnesses to God's goodness that you can give.

735
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:05,000
 Psalm 126, 2 says, "Our mouths were filled with laughter and our tongue with shouts of joy."

736
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:09,000
 Then they said among the nations, "The Lord has done great things for them."

737
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:13,000
 Your laughter could be the best witness you give to people around you.

738
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,000
 Like, Christian, are you listening to me?

739
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:21,000
 Like, the joy you express could cause people to wonder, "What do they know that I don't?"

740
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:24,000
 "Why are they so happy and I'm not?"

741
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:30,000
 "Why is it that when the whole bottom falls out and hell and high water come, they don't give ground at all?"

742
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:35,000
 They're always indomitably joyful.

743
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:37,000
 Your laughter has the power to do that.

744
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:41,000
 Maybe it's storytelling, sitting around and recounting the goodness of God.

745
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:46,000
 Like, all throughout the Gospels, Jesus told parables and stories that he might engage the minds of people

746
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:49,000
 and transform their hearts as they leaned in further to listen.

747
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:57,000
 Maybe it's taking Sabbath, just a regular, repeated, rhythmic break in your schedule

748
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:03,000
 where you don't work, you only play, and you remember that God loves you.

749
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:07,000
 There are so many ways to regularly and rhythmically celebrate what God has done

750
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:09,000
 and cultivate a heart of joy for Jesus.

751
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:15,000
 The issue is not that we lack the ways to do this, it's that we lack the will to do this.

752
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:18,000
 We lack the will.

753
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:24,000
 The irony of this all is that joy is so worthy of wanting.

754
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:27,000
 Don't you want it?

755
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:32,000
 Then why don't we get serious about seeking it?

756
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:41,000
 Joy is not only worthy of wanting, it's desirable, even to the point of discipline.

757
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:47,000
 So let's master ourselves that we might attain that which is most meaningful.

758
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:50,000
 Jesus has come to give you joy.

759
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:55,000
 If you're here and you've lost the art of enjoyment, he has come to give it back to you.

760
00:43:55,000 --> 00:44:02,000
 What we know is that before you can ever lose something, you have to receive something.

761
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:05,000
 Jesus has come to give you joy.

762
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:08,000
 What we know from the scripture is that he came seeing through the eyes of innocence.

763
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:11,000
 He wasn't blind to our sin, he wasn't asleep to our shame,

764
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:17,000
 but remembered how sweet it would be if we had a life with God

765
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,000
 and all the goodness he has to give.

766
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:22,000
 Jesus never graduated from goodness.

767
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:27,000
 Instead, he sacrificed his own goodness for our sake.

768
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:36,000
 He gave himself up on the cross, enduring all the cost of our godlessness

769
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:44,000
 and giving back to us instead all of his godliness.

770
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:50,000
 And Jesus has given us reason to celebrate because though he died and lay dead three days,

771
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:53,000
 he rose forth from the grave.

772
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:56,000
 That's a reason to rejoice.

773
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:58,000
 And it's not a simple one.

774
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,000
 It's so significant.

775
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:05,000
 For in Christ's resurrection hang all the hope of humanity.

776
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:10,000
 They would only place their faith in him.

777
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:13,000
 You want joy?

778
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:15,000
 Joy wants you.

779
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:16,000
 Joy came for you.

780
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:17,000
 Receive him tonight.

781
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:18,000
 Let me pray for us.

782
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:20,000
 God, thank you for this evening.

783
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:25,000
 Thank you for the people here, the work you're doing.

784
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:33,000
 I pray that, God, they would all know you are individually working in their lives

785
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:35,000
 across a full spectrum of spirituality.

786
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:36,000
 Maybe they don't know you, God.

787
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:39,000
 They should know that you're working in their life.

788
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:41,000
 It is not happenstance that they're here tonight.

789
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:46,000
 They're here because you govern all things and you have decided for them to be here.

790
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:53,000
 Maybe they're the firmest in belief, yet, God, they even can experience deeper delight.

791
00:45:53,000 --> 00:46:01,000
 Would we all know, God, that you want to work in our lives, move through our stories,

792
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:05,000
 and lead us into life eternal?

793
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:12,000
 We may have sorrow today, weeping may tarry for the night, but joy comes in the morning.

794
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:14,000
 Joy will come forever and always.

795
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:18,000
 There will be a day when our sorrow and our sadness and our suffering ends,

796
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:22,000
 but all eternity, it'll be bliss because it'll be with you.

797
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,000
 We love you.

798
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:25,000
 It's in Christ's name, amen.

